post_text: Alum Spotlight!
shared_text:
Coddington Physical Therapy, LLC
September 2 at 2:20 PM ¬∑

Coddington and Hickman Physical Therapy are happy to announce the addition of our newest Physical Therapist, Bryce Rolenc, DPT.
Bryce is originally from Seward, NE where he played baseball, football, and wrestled before graduating in 2012 from Seward High School. He graduated in 2016 from Doane College where he majored in Biology and played baseball all 4 years, receiving NAIA scholar athlete honors for 2 years. He attended Physical Therapy school at the University of Nebraska Medical Center in Omaha and graduated with his Doctorate of Physical Therapy in 2019. He worked in a rural town setting where he saw a variety of diagnoses in multiple age ranges before joining us here in Lincoln and Hickman. He enjoys spending time with family and friends, exercising, and playing slow pitch softball in the summer. Bryce is accepting new patients and can also speak Spanish. Call us at 402-423-0303 to schedule an evaluation and check us out on Coddingtonphysicaltherapy.com.

The Department of Agronomy and Horticulture, the Center for Plant Science Innovation, the Center for Root and Rhizobiome Innovation at the University of Nebraska-Lincoln and Nebraska EPSCoR‚Äôs Young Nebraska Scientists organized and funded the very first --- Nebraska Remote Researchers: The Crop Root Microbiomes in Your Backyard summer program.

Juniors Remi Christensen and Natalie Keller were selected to participate, and spent six weeks this summer growing varieties of maize and sorghum. This opportunity allowed them to be introduced to various lab techniques and data collection processes. Their data collection will be used as part of a larger research project within the University of Nebraska.

#sewardjays

Seward County, we need your help to support our schools.

post_text: Seward Elementary is excited to welcome our new kindergarten students to our school during Round Up today! As a reminder: Kindergarten Round Up is from 5:00 - 6:00 PM today. Parents will bring their children in the main entrance and use hand sanitizer before walking children back to their classrooms. All children and adults are required to wear face coverings when entering the building and throughout the time inside the building. Parent Meetings are from 5:00 - 5:30 PM for parents with children in Mrs. Piskorski's and Mrs. Cookus's classes and from 5:30 - 6:00 PM for parents with children in Mrs. Frihauf's, Mrs. St. Louis's, and Mrs. Vancura's classes. When parents are not at their meeting, we ask that they wait outside or in vehicles. Kindergarten students will have Round Up from 5:00 - 6:00 PM (parent meetings are in half hour increments, but children will stay for the full hour). At 6:00 PM, all of the children will be walked out to parents outside of the kindergarten doors. We can't wait to meet our new Bluejays tonight! #sewardjays
